{"author":{"id":"7a44e6dd78392227ec436a4e10846d47c08384a2fec9ddf05df3b184b8053e38"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1686561750,"nonce":"MIltIa+yDGQD3JQOXQzasacxqqU=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s5ochGa","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/5357","origin":"github"},"title":"DESeq2: allow to pass factors and contrast definitions as files as an alternative to UI selections.","message":"My impression is that the current DESeq2 wrapper requires the user to provide the factors and contrasts desired as UI elements, which means that it is very difficult to re-use a workflow that includes DESeq2 because the layout of the workflow and its parameters will depend on the factors and contrasts definitions of each experiment. Towards uses of DESeq2 in a more production oriented manner (where you can re-apply a workflow regardless of the choice of factors and contrasts) it would be nice I think to be able to pass a file (YAML or JSON, possibly the first) to the DESeq2 wrapper as an alternative to the definition of factors and contrasts to the UI. Looking at the source code of the wrapper, it seems to me that the wrapper is already building such file, so I suspect it shouldn't be a lot of effort to optionally just pass it instead of building it there.\n\nIs this an addition that would be welcomed? Thanks.","files":null}]}